The download callback doesn't handle potential errors from chrome.downloads.download. Should check chrome.runtime.lastError and provide proper error handling.
```suggestion
    chrome.downloads.download({ url, filename, saveAs: false }, id => {
      if (chrome.runtime.lastError) {
        console.error('[Offscreen] download failed', chrome.runtime.lastError);
        chrome.runtime.sendMessage({
          type: 'OFFSCREEN_DOWNLOAD_ERROR',
          payload: { message: chrome.runtime.lastError.message },
        });
        URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
        return;
      }
```

[nitpick] The complex runtime check for crypto.randomUUID could be simplified. Modern browsers widely support crypto.randomUUID, and the fallback implementation is already robust. Consider using a simpler check like `crypto.randomUUID?.()` with optional chaining.
```suggestion
  const uuid = globalThis.crypto?.randomUUID?.();
  if (uuid) {
    return uuid;
```

